'' Nonsense ! I'm merely a student at the Opera School here , '' scowled Arkwright . 
Oh , yes , Billy said you were that , but she also said you wouldn't be , long . 
That you'd already had one good offer I'm not speaking of marriage and that you were going abroad next summer , and that they were all insufferably proud of you . 
'' Nonsense ! '' scowled Arkwright , again , coloring like a girl . 
That is only some of of Mrs. Henshaw's kind flattery . 
'' Calderwell jerked the cigar from between his lips , and sat suddenly forward in his chair . 
Arkwright , tell me about them . 
